OL,3,CMen accused of taking part in violent
OL,4,Cdisorder in Hartlepool appear in court
OL,6,FPolice tried to keep order and came
OL,7,Funder attack from bricks, eggs and
OL,8,Fother weapons.
OL,10,FDisorder lasted for several hours and
OL,11,Fa police car was torched, Mr Downey
OL,12,Fsaid.
OL,14,FDistrict Judge Helen Cousins refused
OL,15,Fbail for Anthony Allen and James
OL,16,FElliott.
OL,18,FWhen the judge gave her decision about
OL,19,FAllen, there was an outburst from the
OL,20,Fpublic gallery, with someone shouting
OL,21,F"Out of order".
